association: [{'name': 'Gastrointestinal stromal tumor (GIST)', 'description': 'Common mesenchymal neoplasms arising in the gastrointestinal tract, most often in the stomach. They are histologically, immunohistochemically, and genetically different from typical leiomyomas, leiomyosarcomas, and schwannomas. Most GISTs are composed of a fairly uniform population of spindle-shaped cells. Some tumors are dominated by epithelioid cells or contain a mixture of spindle and epithelioid morphologies. Primary GISTs in the gastrointestinal tract commonly metastasize in the omentum and mesenteries, often as multiple nodules. However, primary tumors may also occur outside of the gastrointestinal tract, in other intra-abdominal locations, especially in the omentum and mesentery.', 'dbReferences': [{'name': 'MIM', 'id': '606764', 'url': 'https://www.omim.org/entry/606764'}], 'evidences': [{'code': 'ECO:0000269', 'source': {'name': 'pubmed', 'id': '11505412', 'url': 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11505412', 'alternativeUrl': 'https://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/11505412'}}, {'code': 'ECO:0000269', 'source': {'name': 'pubmed', 'id': '15824741', 'url': 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15824741', 'alternativeUrl': 'https://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/15824741'}}, {'code': 'ECO:0000269', 'source': {'name': 'pubmed', 'id': '9438854', 'url': 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9438854', 'alternativeUrl': 'https://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/9438854'}}, {'code': 'ECO:0000269', 'source': {'name': 'pubmed', 'id': '9697690', 'url': 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9697690', 'alternativeUrl': 'https://europepmc.org/abstract/MED/9697690'}}], 'disease': True}]
